<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-04-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-04-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="237" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Ambassador <persName type="to">Rockhill</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-18"><hi rend="italic">April 18,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Knox communicates to Mr. Rockhill a brief résumé of the long
                            memorandum handed to-day to the Russian ambassador in Washington and
                            directs Mr. Rockhill to communicate the resume to the American embassies
                            in France, Great Britain, and Germany for their information.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>